COVID-19: The Daily Report

6/20/2020

This Rmarkdown file is intended to give a visual snapshot of the progression of coronavirus: by state, by region, or in total. Data is graciously provided by the NY Times (accessible via Github). Source code for this file can be found on Github.

The most recent date of available information is June 30, 2020.

TO DO: This report can be easily refreshed by simply clicking the Knit button in RStudio - but a self-updating dashboard would be even better.

Regional progression

The US Census Bureau provides regional classifications to us - link - which I will use. Its 1) easy, and 2) seems good enough to identify general trends. Notably, the other category includes Hawaii, Alaska, Puerto Rico, and the Northern Mariana Islands.
